		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=2076"><span id=Sacrifical Lamb>Pusbag</span></a><b><span id=Sacrifical Lamb><br>Sacrifical Lamb</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>9181 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.08]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Totem&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Neither one if you ask me.&nbsp;&nbsp;I would recommend placing your points into STAMINA instead since it gives a monk several attributes which are highly prized.<br>The first benefit which STA gives is a modest one: extra health points every level.  The amount may not be a large amount, but if I had a platinum piece for every time I almost killed a mob but died instead by a few hp, I could have purchased that Tranq staff when I was L20!<br>The second benefit is your endurance in things like running and swimming is increased so that you don't tire as easily.<br>And the third benefit, which is related to the second, is that in this stage of EQ monks are encouraged to fight with weapons early on in their life.  The use of weapons in fights with multiple mobs will tire you out if your STA is less than 100 and will subject you to the proverbial open can of Whoopass (tm) and all the accompanying bad side effects that come with it.<br><br>So, in direct contradiction to what the EQ manual and other sites might tell you, I would encourage to consider STAMINA, especially since AGILITY above 75 produces little in that AC is not dramatically increased.  Monks do not have decent weapons that proc early on, so DEXTERITY points are wasted particularly since items are easily purchased to increase that stat.<br>Of coarse, this is just my opinion and is by no means the final word on this subject.  <br><br>--Pusbag Infection</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>first to 10k in a manner other than shameless spamming on the Last thread gets to be the goldenboy. oh wait, that could have been you...if you weren't a damned post whore, you @#%^in' wanker. --Skeeter</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
