		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=4986"><span id=Scholar>Alerithon</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>92 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Alerithon&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>This is an age old debate.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most folks say either str or agi, with a smaller faction holding out for dex.  I've not seen a sta vote until today, so that's a new one.<br><br>Str increases the number of times you do max damamge.  And your carrying wt limit, which is next to useless unless you've hired yourself out as a mule.  Agi adds to you ac bonus, which goes up with each level.  High reduces the number of times you get hit, and the damage you take when you get hit.<br><br>Sta adds HP and fatigue.  If you're watching your wt., you should'nt have to worry about fatigue.  And those extra hp might help keep you alive on hit longer.<br><br>Dex will make weapons proc more, but don't expect that to happen until you hit level 20 at least.  It also affects thrown weapons.  That's about it.<br><br>Whether you go with Str, Agi, or Sta depends on what you're planning on doing.  Monks work best in a group imo.  Extra sta will help if you solo a lot, but your points would better be spent in str or agi if you take the traditional role of group puller.  <br><br>I put more of my points into agi.  Monks rule in damage over time.  That means to me that it's more important to last in a fight.  We can't take hits like warriors can, so we need to make the mobs miss as much as we can, or ruduce those hits to 1-10 points instead of 30-40 points.  AGI does this.  I can live with not hitting for max every other time, if I can live long enough to get in those 10 extra hits.  <br><br>Hope this helps. =)</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Alerithon Tigerspirit<br>29 rank monk, E'Ci<br>Avatara</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
